law.text:
The examination required in KRS 334.060 shall consist of:
Tests of knowledge pertaining to fitting of hearing instruments including:
Basic physics of sound;
The anatomy and physiology of the ear, including the science of hearing causes and rehabilitation of abnormal hearing and hearing disorders; and
The function of hearing instruments.
Practical tests of proficiency in the following techniques pertaining to the fitting of hearing instruments:
Pure tone audiometry, including air conduction testing and bone conduction testing;
Speech audiometry, including live voice or recorded voice speech evaluations which include speech reception threshold testing, most comfortable listening level, loudness discomfort level, and speech discrimination testing;
Masking when indicated;
Recording and evaluation of audiograms and speech audiometry to determine proper selection and adaption of a hearing instrument; and
Taking earmold impressions.
